en-us: This includes those who work in the following roles: First Responders; PK-12 staff; early childhood education and childcare workers; Frontline essential workers in food, agriculture, distribution, and manufacturing sectors who live or work in non-social distanced settings; Government officials, including staff, engaged in business at the State Capitol; Inspectors responsible for health, life and safety; Correctional facility staff and individuals incarcerated
es-us: Esto incluye a aquellos que trabajan en los siguientes roles: Socorristas; Personal de PK-12; trabajadores de educación infantil y cuidado de niños; Trabajadores esenciales de primera línea en los sectores de la alimentación, la agricultura, la distribución y la fabricación que viven o trabajan en entornos no sociales a distancia; Funcionarios gubernamentales, incluido el personal, se dedicaban a los negocios en el Capitolio estatal; Inspectores responsables de la salud, la vida y la seguridad; Personal del centro correccional y personas encarceladas

en-us: This includes individuals with disabilities living in home settings and their direct care staff
es-us: Esto incluye a las personas con discapacidades que viven en entornos domésticos y su personal de atención directa

en-us:
This includes:
- Cancer
- Chronic kidney disease
- Chronic lung diseases, including COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease), asthma (moderate-to-severe), interstitial lung disease, cystic fibrosis, and pulmonary hypertension
- Dementia or other neurological conditions
- Diabetes (type 1 or type 2)
- Down syndrome
- Heart conditions (such as heart failure, coronary artery disease, cardiomyopathies or hypertension)
- HIV infection
- Immunocompromised state (weakened immune system)
- Liver disease
- Overweight and obesity
- Pregnancy
- Sickle cell disease or thalassemia
- Smoking, current or former
- Solid organ or blood stem cell transplant
- Stroke or cerebrovascular disease, which affects blood flow to the brain
- Substance use disorders

Vaccine providers will ask Iowans to attest to having one of the conditions outlined by the CDC that would put them at greater risk for illness as a result of the COVID-19 virus. Providers will not require additional documentation.
This includes individuals with disabilities who are living in a home setting, and their direct care staff. Your case manager will help coordinate your vaccine.
